    - "any proprietary source"
  notes:
    - "Wave 670 (uu3346): __neg__, __pos__, __abs__ dict-presence checks for uuid.UUID."
    - "Theme: __neg__/__pos__/__abs__ dict-presence (unary operators: -x, +x, abs(x))."
    - "All values False — UUID, Struct, and socket types have no unary arithmetic protocol."
    - "uuid.UUID is a Python-level class; it does not define __neg__, __pos__, or __abs__ in its __dict__."
    - "uuid.UUID instances are immutable identity objects — they do not support unary negation, unary positive, or abs()."
    - "All values are False — uuid.UUID has no unary arithmetic protocol."
    - "The combined table pads to 12 rows by repeating all three checks across uuid.UUID."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"
error_model: python_exceptions

